fcri-Metzgete]]\n: 6th [[1981 Brabantse Pijl|De Brabantse Pijl]]\n: 7th [[1981 UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Men's road race|Road race]], [[1981 UCI Road World Championships|UCI World Championships]]\n: 7th [[1981 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]]\n: 9th [[Grand Prix des Nations]]\n: 10th [[1981 Paris\u2013Roubaix|Paris\u2013Roubaix]]\n;1982\n: 1st [[1982 Omloop Het Volk|Omloop Het Volk]]\n: 1st Sassari\u2013Cagliari\n: 1st Stage 1a [[Three Days of Bruges\u2013De Panne]]\n: 2nd [[Grote Prijs Jef Scherens]]\n: 2nd [[1982 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 3rd [[1982 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n: 3rd [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Road race]], National Road Championships\n: 3rd [[Ronde van Limburg (Belgium)|Ronde van Limburg]]\n: 4th [[Rund um den Henninger Turm]]\n: 8th Overall [[Four Days of Dunkirk]]\n::1st Stage 5a\n: 10th [[1983 La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne|La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n;1983\n: 1st [[1983 Omloop Het Volk|Omloop Het Volk]]\n: 1st [[Coppa Ugo Agostoni]]\n: 1st [[Giro della Romagna]]\n: 1st [[Giro di Toscana]]\n: 1st Stage 2 [[Giro del Trentino]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Setmana Catalana de Ciclisme]]\n: 5th Overall [[Giro di Sardegna]]\n: 8th [[1983 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 9th [[1983 La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne|La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n;1984\n: 1st Stage 14 [[1984 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n: 1st Stage 6 [[Tour of Norway (1980s)|Tour of Norway]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[1984 Tour de Romandie|Tour de Romandie]]\n: 1st Stage 3 [[Vuelta a Andalucia]]\n: 9th [[GP Eddy Merckx]]\n;1985\n: 1st Stage 9 [[1985 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n: 1st Stage 2 [[Vuelta Ciclista a la Comunidad Valenciana]]\n;1986\n: 6th [[1986 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]]\n: 9th [[1986 Brabantse Pijl|De Brabantse Pijl]]\n;1988\n: 2nd [[1988 Dwars door Vlaanderen|Dwars door Vlaanderen]]\n: 7th [[1988 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n;1989\n: 3rd [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Road race]], National Road Championships\n;1990\n: 7th [[Nokere Koerse]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|8811}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100716173843/http://www.letour.fr/HISTO/us/TDF/coureur/4512.html Official Tour de France results for Alfons De Wolf]\n\n{{Milan\u2013San Remo winners}}\n{{Giro di Lombardia winners}}\n{{Vuelta Espa\u00f1a Points Classification}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:De Wolf, Alfons}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Belgian Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Belgian Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Funeral directors]]\n[[Category:People from Willebroek]]\n[[Category:Tour de Suisse stage winners]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp (province)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Alfons De Wolf\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Alfons De Wolf\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1956|6|22}}\n| birth_place   = [[Willebroek]], Belgium\n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     = Classics specialist\n| amateuryears1 = 1978\n| amateurteam1  = {{ct|IJsboerke|1979}} ''(stagiaire)''\n| proyears1     = 1979\u20131980\n| proteam1      = {{ct|Boule d'Or|1979}}\n| proyears2     = 1981\u20131982\n| proteam2      = {{ct|Vermeer Thijs|1981}}\n| proyears3     = 1983\n| proteam3      = {{ct|Bianchi|1983}}\n| proyears4     = 1984\n| proteam4      = {{ct|Europ Decor|1984}}\n| proyears5     = 1985\n| proteam5      = {{ct|Fagor2|1985}}\n| proyears6     = 1986\n| proteam6      = Skala\u2013Skil\n| proyears7     = 1987\u20131989\n| proteam7      = {{ct|AD Renting|1987}}\n| proyears8     = 1990\n| proteam8      = {{ct|Tulip|1990}}\n| majorwins     = [[Giro di Lombardia]] ([[1980 Giro di Lombardia|1980]])<br>[[Milan\u2013San Remo]] ([[1981 Milan\u2013San Remo|1981]])<br>[[Tour de France]], 1 stage<br>[[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]], 5 stages<br>\n:Points classification ([[1979 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|1979]])\n}}\n'''Alfons (\"Fons\") De Wolf''' (born 22 June 1956 in [[Willebroek]]) is a retired [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[bicycle racing|road race cyclist]], a professional from 1979 to 1990. He represented his country at the [[1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Montreal, Quebec]], Canada.<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/de/fons-de-wolf-1.html |title=Alfons De Wolf Olympic Results |accessdate=22 April 2015 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>\n\nHe was forecast, with [[Daniel Willems]], to be the successor to [[Eddy Merckx]]. De Wolf seemed to fulfill that promise by having an absolutely dominant [[1979 Vuelta a Espana]] winning 5 stages including an individual time trial as well as the Points Classification, securing a top 10 place in the General Classification and then following it up by winning the 1980 [[Giro di Lombardia]] and the 1981 [[Milan\u2013San Remo]], the last and first classic of the season. He almost won the 1982 [[Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]], beaten by Italian [[Silvano Contini]] in the final sprint.\n\nAfter winning a stage in the 1984 [[Tour de France]], his career faded. He helped his teammate [[Eddy Planckaert]] win the [[green jersey]] in the [[1988 Tour de France]]. He ended his career in 1990.\n\nHe now helps his wife in her funeral parlour in [[Dworp]], in the south of [[Brussels]].\n\nAlthough he won the [[Omloop Het Nieuwsblad|Omloop Het Volk]] two times, De Wolf was an atypical Flemish cyclist, preferring Italian races such as Milan\u2013San Remo to [[Paris\u2013Roubaix]], [[Gent\u2013Wevelgem]] and the [[Tour of Flanders]]. He was at ease in hilly races, though he was not an impressive climber.\n\nHe complained that he was seen as a 'new Eddy Merckx', that the public had expected too much.\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n;1976\n: 1st Tour de Namur\n: 3rd [[Ronde van Vlaanderen Beloften]]\n: 4th [[Cycling at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual road race|Road race]], [[1976 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]]\n;1977\n: 1st [[Kattekoers]]\n: 3rd [[Ronde van Vlaanderen Beloften]]\n;1978\n: 1st [[Paris\u2013Roubaix Espoirs]]\n: 1st [[File:MaillotB\u00e9lgica.svg|20px]] [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Road race]], National Amateur Road Championships\n: 2nd Overall [[GP Tell]]\n: 2nd [[Circuit de Wallonie]]\n: 2nd [[Fl\u00e8che Ardennaise]]\n: 2nd [[Kattekoers]]\n;1979\n: 1st Omloop Schelde-Durme\n: 2nd [[Trofeo Baracchi]] (with [[Jan van Houwelingen]])\n: 2nd Leeuwse Pijl\n: 3rd Overall [[Tour of Belgium]]\n: 3rd [[Scheldeprijs]]\n: 4th Overall [[Three Days of Bruges\u2013De Panne]]\n: 5th [[1979 La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne|La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n: 7th [[1979 Brabantse Pijl|De Brabantse Pijl]]\n: 8th [[1979 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 9th Overall [[1979 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n::1st {{cjersey|blue}} [[points classification in the Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Points classification]]\n::1st Stages 2, 7, 9, 16b & 19\n: 9th Overall [[1979 Tirreno\u2013Adriatico|Tirreno\u2013Adriatico]]\n: 9th [[1979 Paris\u2013Roubaix|Paris\u2013Roubaix]]\n;1980\n: 1st [[Druivenkoers Overijse]]\n: 1st [[1980 Giro di Lombardia|Giro di Lombardia]]\n: 1st [[Trofeo Baracchi]] (with [[Jean-Luc Vandenbroucke]])\n: 2nd Overall [[1980 Tirreno\u2013Adriatico|Tirreno\u2013Adriatico]]\n: 2nd [[1980 Amstel Gold Race|Amstel Gold Race]]\n: 2nd [[1980 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n: 2nd [[Circuit des Fronti\u00e8res]]\n: 3rd [[Rund um den Henninger Turm]]\n: 3rd Overall [[Vuelta a Mallorca]]\n: 4th [[1980 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 4th [[GP de Fourmies]]\n: 5th Overall [[Giro di Sardegna]]\n: 6th [[1980 Paris\u2013Roubaix|Paris\u2013Roubaix]]\n: 6th [[Grand Prix des Nations]]\n: 6th [[Z\u00fcri-Metzgete]]\n: 7th [[1980 Omloop Het Volk|Omloop Het Volk]]\n: 8th [[Paris\u2013Brussels]]\n: 10th [[1980 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]]\n: 10th [[1980 Milan\u2013San Remo|Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n;1981\n: 1st [[Six Days of Antwerp]] (with [[Ren\u00e9 Pijnen]])\n: 1st [[1981 Milan\u2013San Remo|Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n: 1st [[Circuit des Fronti\u00e8res]]\n: 1st Polder\u2013Kempen\n: 1st Stage 4 [[Tour of Belgium]]\n: 1st Stage 6 [[1981 Tour de Suisse|Tour de Suisse]]\n: 2nd [[GP Eddy Merckx]]\n: 3rd Overall [[1981 Paris\u2013Nice|Paris\u2013Nice]]\n: 3rd [[1981 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n: 3rd [[1981 Amstel Gold Race|Amstel Gold Race]]\n: 3rd [[1981 E3 Harelbeke| E3 Harelbeke]]\n: 5th Overall [[Deutschland Tour]]\n: 5th [[Z\u00fcri-Metzgete]]\n: 6th [[1981 Brabantse Pijl|De Brabantse Pijl]]\n: 7th [[1981 UCI Road World Championships \u2013 Men's road race|Road race]], [[1981 UCI Road World Championships|UCI World Championships]]\n: 7th [[1981 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]]\n: 9th [[Grand Prix des Nations]]\n: 10th [[1981 Paris\u2013Roubaix|Paris\u2013Roubaix]]\n;1982\n: 1st [[1982 Omloop Het Volk|Omloop Het Volk]]\n: 1st Sassari\u2013Cagliari\n: 1st Stage 1a [[Three Days of Bruges\u2013De Panne]]\n: 2nd [[Grote Prijs Jef Scherens]]\n: 2nd [[1982 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 3rd [[1982 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n: 3rd [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Road race]], National Road Championships\n: 3rd [[Ronde van Limburg (Belgium)|Ronde van Limburg]]\n: 4th [[Rund um den Henninger Turm]]\n: 8th Overall [[Four Days of Dunkirk]]\n::1st Stage 5a\n: 10th [[1983 La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne|La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n;1983\n: 1st [[1983 Omloop Het Volk|Omloop Het Volk]]\n: 1st [[Coppa Ugo Agostoni]]\n: 1st [[Giro della Romagna]]\n: 1st [[Giro di Toscana]]\n: 1st Stage 2 [[Giro del Trentino]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Setmana Catalana de Ciclisme]]\n: 5th Overall [[Giro di Sardegna]]\n: 8th [[1983 Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge|Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n: 9th [[1983 La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne|La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n;1984\n: 1st Stage 14 [[1984 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n: 1st Stage 6 [[Tour of Norway (1980s)|Tour of Norway]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[1984 Tour de Romandie|Tour de Romandie]]\n: 1st Stage 3 [[Vuelta a Andalucia]]\n: 9th [[GP Eddy Merckx]]\n;1985\n: 1st Stage 9 [[1985 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n: 1st Stage 2 [[Vuelta Ciclista a la Comunidad Valenciana]]\n;1986\n: 6th [[1986 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]]\n: 9th [[1986 Brabantse Pijl|De Brabantse Pijl]]\n;1988\n: 2nd [[1988 Dwars door Vlaanderen|Dwars door Vlaanderen]]\n: 7th [[1988 Gent\u2013Wevelgem|Gent\u2013Wevelgem]]\n;1989\n: 3rd [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Road race]], National Road Championships\n;1990\n: 7th [[Nokere Koerse]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|8811}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100716173843/http://www.letour.fr/HISTO/us/TDF/coureur/4512.html Official Tour de France results for Alfons De Wolf]\n\n{{Milan\u2013San Remo winners}}\n{{Giro di Lombardia winners}}\n{{Vuelta Espa\u00f1a Points Classification}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:De Wolf, Alfons}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Belgian Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Belgian Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Funeral directors]]\n[[Category:People from Willebroek]]\n[[Category:Tour de Suisse stage winners]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a 