\n| team           = Chicago Bulls\n| end_year       = 2016\n| wins           = 42\n| losses         = 40\n| division       = Central\n| division_place = 4\n| conf_place     = 9\n| coach          = [[Fred Hoiberg]]\n| gm             = [[Gar Forman]]\n| owners         = \n| arena          = [[United Center]]\n| bbr_team       = CHI\n| television     = [[Comcast SportsNet Chicago|CSN Chicago]]<br />[[WGN-TV|WGN]]<br />[[WCIU-TV|WCIU]]\n| radio          = [[WMVP]]\n| playoffs       = ''Did not qualify''\n}}\nThe '''[[2015\u201316 NBA season|2015\u201316]] [[Chicago Bulls]] season''' was the 50th season of the franchise in the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA). [[Fred Hoiberg]] was selected as the head coach, after the firing of previous head coach [[Tom Thibodeau]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=SELIGMAN|first1=ANDREW|title=Chicago Bulls introduce Fred Hoiberg as new coach|url=https://news.yahoo.com/chicago-bulls-introduce-fred-hoiberg-coach-191002388--spt.html|website=[[Yahoo! News]] via [[Associated Press]]|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Jimmy Butler (basketball)|Jimmy Butler]], for the second time was voted to play in the [[2016 NBA All-Star Game]], which was held in Toronto. However, Butler was unable to play due to injury and replacing him was teammate [[Pau Gasol]].\n\n[[Derrick Rose]] played in 66 games this season, the most since his MVP campaign in [[2010\u201311 NBA season|2010-11.]] Following the season, he was traded to the [[2016-17 New York Knicks season|New York Knicks]], [[Joakim Noah]] signed as a free agent with the Knicks and Gasol signed with the [[2016-17 San Antonio Spurs season|San Antonio Spurs]].\n\nThe Bulls missed the playoffs for the first time since [[2007-08 Chicago Bulls season|2008]] and were eliminated from playoff contention by the [[2015-16 Detroit Pistons season|Detroit Pistons]].\n\n==Draft picks==\n{{main|2015 NBA Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable sortable\" \n! style=\"background:#C41E3A;\" 